        "timestamp": "2020-01-28 12:37:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: -Code-Review\n\n> Samuli, All the SQL capabilities should be using the processor-db\n > properties for accessing mysql tables in SDN-C in Frankfurt\n > release. There is no need to use endpoint selector for this.\n > \n > WHat is the reason to bring back endpoint selector??\n\nOK, good to know. But how we could know that? I did not found any such info and only \"documentation\" is the existing use cases in cds repo and existing starter-dictionary. E.g. it's used in vFW: https://github.com/onap/ccsdk-cds/blob/4786e0b9ef3b4b82f4ad14bcffafa222628011d6/ms/blueprintsprocessor/application/src/main/resources/application.properties#L50-L54 and many starter-dictionary DDs has it.\n\nI can change this to other way round and remove usage from all use cases?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
